                3 The Holy Ghost is a Spirit of Power in us, by being in us a Spirit of Wisdome: and so it is,
A Spirit of Wisdome. because it makes us wise with the wisdome of God, wise upon earth after the rate of heaven, wise to Salvation. There is no man wise without the Spirit of God; for the wisdome of carnall men is but foolishnesse before God, yea before Angels and Saints, but the wisdome of the Spirit is most gracious and heavenly wisdome. And this wisdome of the Spirit is the strength of a Christian: the more he hath of it, the more mighty he is, both in all his doings and indurings. It is said, Eccles. 9.15. That there was a poore wise man, delivered a small city from the power of a mighty King, and therefore Solomon concludes that wisdome is better then strength, for it can do greater things then strength can. When David carried himselfe wisely, Saul a great King was afraid of him: he thought himself too weak to deale with David, and David too mighty to deale with him, because of his wisdome: and Solomon asked Wisdom of God above all things for the strength of his government;
2 Cor. 1 10. all government without this being but weak and brittle. This wisdome contributes strength to us, whereas we say of a man that wants wisdome, he is a weake man: And so the Holy Ghost being a Spirit of wisdome in us, is also a Spirit of Power.

                1. Without this power of the spirit, Ministers are utterly unable to preach the Word;
               They are unable to preach the VVord. the true, spirituall, living Word of God. For to preach this Word of God, requires the Power of God. One may speak the word of man by the power of man, but he cannot speak the Word of God, but by the power of God. And Christ himself in all his Ministerie spake nothing of himself, in the strength of his humane nature, but he spake all he spake by the power of God; and without this power of God, he could not have spoken one word of God. And so in like manner, no man is able to preach Christ but by the Holy Ghost, which is the power of God. For Christ is the power of God, and can never be represented, but by the Holy Ghost which is the power of God. For as we see light in his light, that

is, the Father who is light, in the Son who is light; or else the Son who is light, in the Holy Ghost who is light; So we know power in his power, that is the Son who is power, in the Holy Ghost who is power. And Christ who is the power of God, can never be made known to the Church, but by the ministration of the spirit, which is the power of God. So that it is not an easie thing to preach Christ the power of God, yea none can do it aright, but by the power of the Holy Ghost comming upon him.



                1. The whose body of sin, in all the parts and members and branches of it;
The whole body of sin. each severall influence and operation of the spirit being a severall destruction of some sin or other. For as the spirit that is in us lusts after envy, or pride, or vainglory, or covetuousnesse, or uncleannesse or the like; so the Spirit we have of God according to its mighty power, destroyes all those sinfull workes of our corrupt Spirit, and mortifies all the deeds of our flesh,
Rom. 8.13. according to that of Paul, if yee mortify the deeds of the flesh by the Spirit, ye shall live: The flesh will never mortify its own deeds, but the spirit must mortify the deeds of the flesh, and this will mortify them according to the whole Latitude of them.

So that we cannot by any acts of our owne prepare our selves to receive the Spirit;
Wherein it doth. but only by the Spirit we prepare our selves to receive the Spirit. For it is not any worke of our owne upon our selves, but the immediate worke of the Holy Ghost upon us, that can make us fit to receive himselfe. It lyes wholly in his owne power and goodnesse, first to prepare in us a place for himselfe, and then after to receive and entertaine

himselfe in that place he hath so prepared. Now the workes of the Spirit, whereby he first prepares us for himselfe, and then entertaines himselfe in us, are these two especially.
